nt color=#A62A2A>(8/26/02 2:51:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1264.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Clerics, have no fear!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Why should a druid or shaman only be 40%(if even) as effective at healing compared to a cleric?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Clerics do 1 thing... heal people.<br>
<br>
In the case of druids, they have the following list of abilities..<br>
<br>
quadding, snaring, sow, ports, defensive buffs (different but in many cases preferable to a clerics), Nukes (2nd only to wizards I believe), invis, see invis, succor<br>
<br>
I think the question should really be, Why are they even allowed to heal at 40% the capability of a class whose SOUL purpose is to heal.... sounds a little overpowered to me.<br>
<br>
In the case of Shaman, they have the following list of abilities...<br>
<br>
Invis, see invis, Shrink, sow, SLOW, torpor, canni.<br>
<br>
Same argument as druids...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I can't imagine who would play a paladin if they were only 40% as good at tanking as warriors.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This depends on what you are talking about... In most high end raid situations a paladin can't tank period.  Warrior / paladin is almost the same situation as cleric / druid.  You play a paladin because it's easy to solo, they have fun spells, and you can whack stuff and tank pretty good.  You play a warrior if you want to know for 100% certainty that high ends cannot survive without you.  Same story for clerics / druids.. You play a cleric because you KNOW that once you get to the end, you will be needed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This does not break the cleric class at all. It only provides a group with more flexibility by allowing a druid or shaman to be main healer if necessary. This is nothing new to every other class in the game except maybe clerics. A paladin, SK, monk have been able to replace a warrior as main tank for a long time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again you're only looking at xp groups.. I have a news flash.  If xp were the only thing in Everquest, there would not be one single person playing a cleric anywhere.  You don't NEED a cleric for most xp situations as it is now.. Shamans / druids can replace them just fine and add much more to the group than just a guy who stands up every 5 minutes and casts CH.  No cleric is concerned about how this affects our &quot;groupability&quot;, we're already passed up for Shamen and Druids as it is in a lot of situations.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I have to say I totally disagree with your argument.  You saw the list of abilities up above.. If druids / shaman can suddenly replace a cleric for healing.. please tell me why you would EVER have a cleric in your group over a shaman or a druid.  Do the math..<br>
<br>
The real problem is Verant is going about this the entirely wrong way.. They are looking at demographics.  What classes are being played, what classes aren't.. The flat out said they are making these changes because too many raids are being cancelled due to lack of clerics.. <br>
<br>
The solution is to make people actually WANT to play clerics.. Not make druids and shamen able to do our job for us.  I hope you are real friendly with a lot of clerics, because if these changes happen, you will see clerics quitting left and right... there just won't be a point to playing a cleric anymore.<br>
<br>
Xylox<br>
